JoJo Siwa has addressed her rekindled romance with ex Kylie Prew after the couple confirmed they were back together. The Dance Moms star, 18, had been in a relationship with Kylie for nine months until their break-up in October 2021, but the pair are back together and stronger than ever. JoJo told Entertainment Tonight: ‘I am in a relationship and I’m very happy and very lucky to be loved. It’s been very nice. ‘I think something that’s been great, is it’s been so honest, and I think that’s a mistake that I’ve made in the past, is maybe trying to be something that I maybe wasn’t. ‘But this is just so pure and so honest, and it’s so real and it just feels like I/we got it right.’ JoJo had first hinted that things might be back on with Kylie in April when she told Extra she was ‘very much in love.’ She said at the time: ‘I’m very happy. I’m very much in love. I… am really lucky that I’m loved unconditionally, too, by this human, and she is awesome. ‘It would be really nice if she was at my home. We’re long-distance, which is always hard. She is the best, and FaceTimes and when we do actually get to see each other, my heart is just like…’ JoJo remained coy at the time about whether the person in question was Kylie, admitting she should have asked her ‘what she wanted me to say’ before doing press. The pair have since appeared in several loved-up posts together on social media, with JoJo posting a snap of her kissing Kylie at Disney World, captioned: ‘If you love something let it go, if it comes back….’ Got a story? If you’ve got a celebrity story, video or pictures get in touch with the Metro.co.uk entertainment team by emailing us celebtips@metro.co.uk, calling 020 3615 2145 or by visiting our Submit Stuff page – we’d love to hear from you. MORE : JoJo Siwa reunites with girlfriend Kylie Prew 7 months after split: ‘If you love something let it go’ MORE : JoJo Siwa claims she ‘wasn’t invited’ to Nickelodeon Kids’ Choice awards 